         <abstract label="Abstract:">Correspondence relating to the collection, classification, and
            study of plant specimens; recommendations for graduate students; notes on the
            development of botanical investigation at Cornell; and diary of a trip to Europe.
            Material relating to Atkinson's work at the University of North Carolina and the
            Agricultural Experiment Station in Auburn, Alabama. </abstract>
         <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language>
         </langmaterial>
      </did>
      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Botanist; Professor, Cornell University.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence relating to the collection, classification, and study of plant specimens;
            recommendations for graduate students; notes on the development of botanical
            investigation at Cornell; and diary of a trip to Europe. Also, a bound volume of
            reprints, notes, and correspondence relating to Atkinson's work between 1886 and 1890 at
            the University of North Carolina and the Agricultural Experiment Station in Auburn,
            Alabama. Includes correspondence with Margaret Clay Ferguson (BS '99, Ph.D. '01). Also,
            platinum print photograph of students and faculty, inscribed to "Prof. George F.
            Atkinson with best regards of the Hindu students, Cornell University, 24 June 1907."</p>
         <p>Index of correspondence available in accession folder.</p>
      </scopecontent>
